70
00:03:51,097 --> 00:03:52,565
<i>As for Matsushima,</i>

71
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:56,469
<i>what was he feeling about
returning to this place?</i>

72
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,638
Uh...

73
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,442
This is my first time
talking about it, but...

74
00:04:03,109 --> 00:04:07,113
I had never really, in elementary school,

75
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:10,083
or in my childhood...

76
00:04:10,149 --> 00:04:15,121
I never really had things I liked doing,
or things I wanted to do.

77
00:04:15,688 --> 00:04:19,525
Everyone was in soccer clubs and...

78
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,929
the tennis club or something.

79
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:26,799
Everyone was doing what they wanted,
but I didn't have that.

80
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:30,803
I was wondering what my future held

81
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:37,410
and I happened to see
Hey! Say! JUMP's debut concert DVD.

82
00:04:38,211 --> 00:04:42,348
I was like, "Wow, who's that?"
And that started it.

83
00:04:43,850 --> 00:04:46,252
{\an8}<i>He entered Johnny's at age 13.</i>

84
00:04:46,319 --> 00:04:49,589
{\an8}<i>His debut was about six months later.</i>

85
00:04:50,723 --> 00:04:54,327
{\an8}<i>Thinking back,
he says he was missing something.</i>

86
00:04:56,095 --> 00:04:58,631
The other four bandmates,

87
00:04:58,698 --> 00:05:02,001
they had a certain determination
for doing the job,

88
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:05,438
but I didn't have that determination yet.

89
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:11,277
Especially Fuma and Kento, they'd been
in Johnny's Jr. for a long time,

90
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:13,413
so they were determined to debut.

91
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:16,549
And they had goals for after that.

92
00:05:16,616 --> 00:05:19,118
They were prepared for how it would be.

93
00:05:19,185 --> 00:05:20,586
But in my case,

94
00:05:20,653 --> 00:05:23,323
I wanted to join Johnny's
and change my life.

95
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:25,825
I just fearlessly jumped in

96
00:05:25,892 --> 00:05:27,560
and I suddenly debuted.

97
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:31,431
I didn't have time to prepare, mentally.

98
00:05:32,465 --> 00:05:35,902
And I didn't even know what work was.

99
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:42,175
A lot of things happened
and I just couldn't keep up.

100
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:46,446
<i>We asked the others about Matsushima.</i>

101
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:50,083
With him, with all things,

102
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:55,588
we wanted him to experience them
in a positive way.

103
00:05:56,489 --> 00:05:58,624
We always thought about that.

104
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:04,263
No matter what So decided to do,

105
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:08,434
I told him I'd support him.

106
00:06:08,501 --> 00:06:14,474
I also told him that
the love I feel for So hasn't changed.

107
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:18,978
<i>They each kept a certain distance
in their own ways.</i>

108
00:06:23,349 --> 00:06:27,653
I had a feeling this song would
get So to come back.

109
00:06:28,988 --> 00:06:30,456
And with this song,

110
00:06:30,523 --> 00:06:34,527
we'd make a comfortable place
for So to return to.

111
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:37,697
{\an8}It's a can of juice for Matsushima.

112
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:42,101
{\an8}Matsushima's here
and we're all taking a break together.

113
00:06:42,168 --> 00:06:44,737
{\an8}We wanted to make that sort of atmosphere.

114
00:06:44,804 --> 00:06:48,374
It's not the answer, but
that's how I see it, anyway.

115
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,443
To keep the pressure off me,

116
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:54,414
they tried to keep a good balance
and I could see that.

117
00:06:55,381 --> 00:06:58,484
That sort of thing made me really happy.

118
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:06,526
It helped me realize,
"I do want to work with those four."

119
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:09,395
I spoke to the people at the agency

120
00:07:09,462 --> 00:07:15,368
and I said, "Let me start talking
to the bandmates again."

121
00:07:16,302 --> 00:07:19,772
So I'm grateful to Mr. Johnny

122
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,608
and I'm grateful to my bandmates.

123
00:07:22,675 --> 00:07:25,378
And to all the fans
who kept supporting me,

124
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,847
of course, I feel gratitude toward them.

125
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:32,485
That's why I wanted to
give this another try.

126
00:07:34,353 --> 00:07:37,390
<i>September 10, Makuhari Messe.</i>

127
00:07:38,357 --> 00:07:41,627
Today's our first time with five.

128
00:07:42,495 --> 00:07:43,796
I'll do my best.

129
00:07:46,199 --> 00:07:49,235
<i>The day finally came.</i>

130
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,737
FIRST PERFORMANCE WITH 5 MEMBERS

131
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:53,673
Two, three, four.

132
00:07:53,739 --> 00:07:57,844
<i>Before the show, they made final
adjustments in a corner of the venue.</i>

133
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,448
Are you okay, So?

134
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:03,749
